<br>
I too have not been in to long so I will comment on what I have seen....<br>
<br>
1. Nobility - Having or showing qualities of high moral character.<br>
Narcotical/Iandias - I have Rithe telling me of very many times in his ranger carrier how she saved his bacon and was a good friend when he needed it.  She also gave me a noct blade when I needed an upgrade from a MOSS for 2k of which I could owe her later.  I have had the money for a month now and she hasn't asked for it, just to keep it for her, which is in Forcy's possession right now, since she lives up there.  I have heard of many times that Iandias has saved several people with her knowledge of Velks either being there, or as of yesterday, from a distance to Toorch.<br>
<br>
2. Honor - Principled uprightness of character<br>
<br>
I would have to say all of the hawks embody this.  I mean this in the most broadest of examples.  I see each of us holding the guild as a whole to be defined by their actions and therefore I have never seen a Silverhawk act inappropriately. <br>
<br>
3. Respect - To feel or show deferential regard for<br>
<br>
Again each Hawk respects each other and others not of our guild.  I can't pinpoint one in particular.<br>
<br>
4. Loyalty - A feeling or attitude of devoted attachment<br>
I'm giving this to Unianu, and seconded by Tygerkat.  The MM raid I put on yesterday, while a tought day, looked bleak as just Unianu and I were sitting there alone with only Asmius trying to get there at 1pm Eastern.  Unianu stuck with me until 5:30 eastern and also ran with me as I tested zone defenses and pathing.  Much like TYgerkat I made her my friend forever that day, and if there is anything she even remotely needs, or needs me to use my body to defend her, I will at anytime (As long as she can pick me up).<br>
<br>
Then Later, my helper on the raid, Tygerkat, on a friends computer, gives me a tell and explains to me why she can not show up.  Her power is out at her house and she is desperately trying to get it fixed.  However in and among the RL crisis, which I totally could understand she could not join us, she sends me tells she cannot show up and apologizes.  I thought that was the most incredible show of loyalty I have ever seen, and she will always be my teddymistress.<br>
<br>
5. Valor - Courage and boldness, as in battle; bravery<br>
A tough one here but I would say HP, I have heard tales and have seen once where he stayed behind to get ripped apart to let the group evac.  <br>
<br>
6. Generosity - Liberality in giving or willingness to give<br>
Vaparaiso - <br>
This is a story related to me by Rithe Silverwind, Forcy's in game brother and my RL best friend:<br>
Apparently the other night, (friday) I believe right before the womens auction, Vap was in DL waiting for  a Karnor's group to take out VS.  This other Druid, and I forget her name was taking an awful long time getting a group together, so Rithe took the friends and guildmembers he had and Vap down into Karnors and they took out VS (quite easily he told me).  Anyhow Rithe looted his stone and told Vap to quickly loot the other one and instead, Vap allowed the druid who was trying to form the group that they killed VS on loot it.  Rithe's group was within its rights to loot since they had a ready force to go and she was not comitting to raiding VS right away, but Vap showed generosity in allowing her to loot a much needed item that he desperately needed.  In my mind there is no higher form of generosity.  Several other things come to mind like honor as well.<br>
<br>
7. Compassion<br>
<br>
Forcythia/Xoel/Tygerkat:<br>
These three represent the compassionate three in my opinion.  I have seen Xoel drop whatever she is doing and go to the aid of a fallen companion.  Or Forcythia sit in FP and give her coin and help to newbie bards instead of leveling.  In fact FOrcy never levels she spends too much time helping everyone...when she doesn;t work in RL.  She grabbed Xoel and sprinted at top speed to Everfrost to rescue RIthe and Trothbashand then back.  She will run all over the place to help....<br>
<br>
Tygerkat, she's my friend and I love her dearly.  She helped make me laugh when I died a lot one day, and in just 15 minutes I was really content.  She will heal and tl anyone who asks and she will always try to be in game and tell someone why she can;t show up.  She makes the most upset person happy with her charm and wit.<br>
<br>
Well that's all I gotta say.  i hope more people reply here its a really good post.<br>
